                    <idno type="BHS">982</idno>
                    <idno type="BHS">981</idno>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-320">
                        <quote source="#bib320-1">Monk, founder and abbot of the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/384">‘Great Monastery’</placeName> on <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/100">Mount Izla</placeName>.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="description">In hagiography: Abraham of Kashkar (Abraham the Great of Kashkar, or "the elder") was a celebrated reformer of monasticism in <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1452">Mesopotamia</persName> and a great saint of the Church of the East. A student of the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/476">School of Nisibis</placeName>, Abraham was a missionary, ascetic, and miracle-worker. He was called "Father of the Monks of the Orient."</note>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib320-4">male</sex>
                    <birth>
                        <date when="0492" syriaca-computed-start="0492-01-01" source="#bib320-4">0492</date>
                        <date notBefore="0475" notAfter="0525" syriaca-computed-end="0525-01-01" syriaca-computed-start="0475-01-01" source="#bib320-1">ca. 500</date>
                    </birth>
                    <death>
                        <date when="0586" syriaca-computed-start="0586-01-01" source="#bib320-4">0586</date>
                        <date when="0588" syriaca-computed-start="0588-01-01" source="#bib320-1">588</date>
                    </death>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib320-4">La commemoraison d' Abraham etait le 2 mai chez les Syriaques orientaux.
Les sources primitives de Ia Vie d'Abraham (Abba Jean et R.abban Rustam) sont
perdues, mais ont ete utilisees par Je Liber castitatis ; par Thomas de Marga,
Liber superiorum, I.4 ; par MarT ibn Sulayman, 47 arabe ; par Ia Chronique de
Seert, II, 41-43 ; par sa Vita editee par Sachau (BHO, 14) ; et par J'Histoire de
Rabban bar 'Idta (ROC 11 [1906], 406-408).
Ses regles ont ete editees en syriaque et traduites en anglais par V66bus, Documents,
150- 62.
Resume dans DHGE, I, col. 174- 75.
BSO, I, 26- 28 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">goes with sergius</note>
                    <note>The commemoration of Abraham was May 2 among the East Syrians.</note>
                    <note>Earliest sources of the Life of Abraham (Abba John and Rabban Rustam) are lost, but they were used by the following:</note>
                    <state type="confession" source="#bib320-1">
                        <desc>Ch. of E.</desc>
                    </state>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib320-4">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
